Hello world example

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Define the x values from 0 to 4*pi
x = np.linspace(0, 4 * np.pi, 1000)

# Compute the y values as the sine of x
y = np.sin(x)

# Create the plot
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))
plt.plot(x, y, label='sin(x)', color='blue')

# Add labels and title
plt.title('Sinusoid Plot for $x$ from 0 to $4\\pi$')
plt.xlabel(r'$x$')
plt.ylabel(r'$\sin(x)$')

# Add a grid and a legend
plt.grid(True)
plt.legend()

# Show the plot
plt.show()
